'''stop codon'''
{{wikipedia}}
#{{biology}}, {{genetics}}, {{biochemistry}} a [[sequence]] of three [[RNA]] [[nucleotide]]s ([[A]], [[C]], [[G]] or [[U]]) that instruct the synthesis, or [[translation]], of a [[protein]] to stop. The three-letter stop codon sequences have been given names: "UAG" is ''[[amber]]'', "UGA" is ''[[opal]]'', and "UAA" is ''[[ochre]]''.